Tippy's features

Default

The default tippy tooltip looks like this when given no options. It has a nifty backdrop filling animation!

Placement

A tippy can be placed in four different ways in relation to its reference element. Additionally, the tippy be shifted.

Arrows

Arrows point toward the reference element. There are two different types of arrows: sharp and round. You can transform the proportion and scale of the arrows any way you like.

Triggers

Triggers define the types of events that cause a tooltip to show.

Interactivity

A tippy can be interactive, meaning it won't hide when you hover over or click on it.

Animations

A tippy can have different types of animations.

Duration

A tippy can have different transition durations.

Delay

A tippy can delay showing or hiding* {' '} after a trigger.

Event delegation

A tippy can delay showing or hiding* {' '} after a trigger.
